  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery guys look for when I exchange my old phone for a new one?",
  "response": "When you exchange an old phone at Flipkart, the delivery person typically checks several aspects of the device:\n\n1. Physical condition\n- No major cracks or damage to the screen\n- No water damage\n- Intact body without significant dents or breaks\n\n2. Functional aspects\n- Device powers on\n- Touchscreen works properly\n- Buttons and ports functioning\n- No hardware issues\n\n3. Technical requirements\n- Original battery\n- No blacklisted IMEI number\n- Not reported as stolen\n- Meets the exchange conditions specified during purchase\n\n4. Accessories\n- Original charger might be required (check specific exchange terms)\n- Basic accessories like SIM tray\n\n5. Data and account status\n- Device should be factory reset\n- Not locked to any specific account\n\nThe exact criteria can vary depending on Flipkart's current exchange policy, the specific model, and the condition grade you selected during the exchange process. It's recommended to carefully read Flipkart's exchange terms and conditions before initiating an exchange.",
